The paper deals with signal recovery from noisy linear measurements, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and signal processing (cs.SI). The use of projected gradient methods and the restricted isometry property also suggest these categories.
